Carasobarbus apoensis was originally described from Khamīs Mushayt, Wadī Turabah and Wadī Adamah as a member of the genus Barbus ( Banister and Clarke 1977 ). It was later transferred to the genus Carasobarbus (
Ekmek-ci and Banarescu 1998
). Alkahem and Behnke (1983) reported an unknown Barbus and tentatively considered these specimens to be atypical Carasobarbus apoensis . We did not find any evidence of an undescribed Carasobarbus species that occurs sympatrically with Carasobarbus apoensis , thus we agree with their conclusion.
